# Changelog

All notable changes to **logic-zig** are documented in this file.

The format is based on [Keep a Changelog](https://keepachangelog.com/en/1.1.0/),
and this project aims to follow [Semantic Versioning](https://semver.org/).

## [0.12.3] — 2026-07-16

### Added

- AIGER goldens: hold_true/false, dual_stuck, and2_bad_ext
- Manifest + builtin expansion → **golden 44/44**
- `logic-hwmcc fair-demo` and **`stack`** (golden + track stuck0)
- Doctor: fair multi, portfolio, drat-trim probe
- CI: sat_hard sample, hwmcc stack, track unsafe fixture
- Builtin: counter BMC, aag/aig write roundtrip, nand unsat, portfolio sat

## [0.12.2] — 2026-07-16

### Added

- More AIGER goldens: `stuck0_b`, `init1_bad`, `const0_safe`, `toggle_justice`
- Expanded manifest + fair multi builtin → **golden 30/30**
- `logic-sat drat-fuzz` external DRAT fuzz loop
- `logic-sat hard` portfolio directory bench
- Fair multi depth: 2J+2F one stuck, justice+fairness toggle, round-robin attach

## [0.12.1] — 2026-07-16

### Added

- AIGER golden fixtures + `corpus/golden/manifest.jsonl`
- `golden.runAll` = builtin + manifest + external DRAT-trim
- Portfolio: 6 configs, ramp budgets, model validation, optional RUP
- Fair multi-justice cases; `logic-sat check-drat` / `portfolio --proof`

## [0.12.0] — 2026-07-16

Core + spin-off product matrix (agent/sat/hwmcc/cert/smt/ctl), CI, certificates, CTL, BV, portfolio, BTOR2.

## [0.11.0] — 2026-07-16

Fair multi-justice, unique MUS, IC3a PDR, full AIG gate lower.

## [0.10.0] — 2026-07-16

Public release: SAT, sequential MC, k-liveness, docs.
